The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and Prime Minister Phúc during a meeting in Vietnam. Prime Minister Phúc expressed appreciation for the efforts towards denuclearization in North Korea and thanked President Trump for choosing Vietnam as the venue for the second summit. He also praised the economic performance of the United States and Vietnam and expressed support for promoting bilateral trade cooperation. President Trump thanked Prime Minister Phúc for his hospitality and praised Vietnam's progress and economic achievements. He expressed optimism about the upcoming meeting with Chairman Kim of North Korea and discussed the potential for North Korea to become a great economic power. President Trump also expressed appreciation for the orders made by Vietnam for Boeing and General Electric aircraft and discussed the possibility of Vietnam purchasing military equipment from the United States. Both leaders expressed friendship and mutual appreciation.